REGULAR.description: Conan, Kogoro, and Ran In Purple Toyota Crown GRS204 Drive pass through Mount Fuyana on their way home and are stopped by Misao Yamamura who instilled a road block in order to catch the Silver Witch, a woman who drives a White FD car and challenges people in a drag race. When the witch drifts, the tire makes a sound that sound like a woman screaming. Yamamura reveals his grandma raced against the witch but gave up when the witch drove into the air. Kogoro decides to investigate on the identity of the witch and returns to Mount Fuyana the next day, taking Conan and Ran with him in Orange Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution X (CZ4A). Upon meeting the witch, Kogoro has a drag race with her but stops when Conan reveals that the witch drove into a road less area. Kogoro tells Yamamura to stop all White FD drivers and wait for his arrival. Once there, Kogoro interrogates the three suspect pairs in order to find out which one of them is the witch.

REGULAR.description:
Sera heads to the rental villa to meet a client with Conan, Ran, and Sonoko. On their way, Ran and Sonoko spot a woman dressed in red from head to toe. At the rental villa, Tamami, Sumika, Ninda, and Hakuya, members of a former high school outdoor club, had gathered. 15 years prior, a wife stabbed her husband to death at a nearby villa.
Source: crunchyroll

Hakuya`s body is discovered, and the Nagano police led by Uehara Yoshie begin their investigation. Uehara believes the culprit struck Hakuya on the back of the head with a blunt object and knocked him unconscious before drowning him in the bathtub.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Tragedy of the Red Woman (Evil Spirit)

REGULAR.description:
Sumika is attacked by someone resembling the Red Woman, but the cut is shallow, and Uehara treats her with antiseptic. Uehara explains there was no mistake in the DNA test of the Red Woman. However, Uehera adds since over ten years ago around this time of year, rental villas in the area are robbed.
Source: crunchyroll

Comedian DoDonPa Rokusuke turns himself in at a police box for the murder of his talent agency`s president Tendo Hideki. True to his testimony, Tendo is discovered at the agency dead from a blow to the head, and DoDonPa claims he struck the president with the metal bat found beside the body.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Comedian Who Turned Himself In (Part 1)

REGULAR.description:
Conan feels something is wrong with DoDonPa`s all too convenient alibi and begins to strongly suspect him. After taking on the guilt for a murder he didn`t commit, DoDonPa becomes the man of the hour for trying to protect the reputation of his benefactor Tendo.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Comedian Who Turned Himself In (Part 2)

REGULAR.description:
Conan, Ran, and Sonoko visit the hotel room where Sera is living. In the hallway on the 30th floor of Sera`s hotel, editors A, B, and C wait for author Hiura Keigo to finish his manuscripts. Later, Hiura`s assistant Minazuki Chiori is found murdered in the room directly below Hiura`s.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Igai na Kekka no Ren`ai Shousetsu (Zenpen)
The Romance Novel with the Unexpected Conclusion (Part 1)

REGULAR.description:
Author Keigo Hiura`s assistant Chiaki Minazuki is found strangled to death in a hotel. Hiura has a perfect alibi, but Conan and Sera are certain he committed the crime. They ask about the condition of Minazuki`s room and get closer to the truth. A 20 year old postcard is discovered inside Minazuki`s suitcase. It is addressed to Hiura, and the sender is not Minazuki but Jun Ota, which is also the name of the heroine in Hiura`s "The Phone, the Ocean, and I". Later a casual remark from Takagi helps Conan and Sera realize how Hiura manipulated his alibi...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Igai na Kekka no Ren`ai Shousetsu (Kouhen)
The Romance Novel with the Unexpected Conclusion (Part 2)

REGULAR.description:
Conan, Kogoro, and Ran arrive in Ishikawa Prefecture`s Kanazawa and are met by tourism agency employees Yuzo Tanimoto and Moeko Miyazawa and event company president Yuya Tadokoro and his employees Osamu Kuranishi and Harumi Akiyama. They have asked for Kogoro`s help with the Kaga Hyakumangoku Mystery Tour city revitalization event to be held in the Kanazawa.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Kaga Hyakuman Ishi Mystery Tour (Kanazawa Hen)
Kaga Hyakumangoku Mystery Tour 1re partie : Kanazawa

REGULAR.description:
Ran accompanies Akiyama to the hospital after she is attacked while Kogoro and the others continue visiting the checkpoints. After arriving at the Kanazawa 21st Century Museum, Conan chckes the four cards that fell out of Akiyama`s bag.
Source: crunchyroll

Kaga Hyakumangoku Mystery Tour (Kaga Hot Springs Arc)
Kaga Hyakumangoku Mystery Tour. 2e partie : les bains de Kaga

REGULAR.description:
On a rainy day, Conan bumps into a suspicious man being purused by police. The man is a drug dealer, and he drops his notebook as he flees. The notebook contains a code written using subway station and line numbers, but some of the code washed away in the rain.
Source: crunchyroll

Conan et Heiji, le code de l`amour (1re partie)
Conan to Heiji: Koi no Angou (Zenpen)

When Heiji arrives at Nihonbashi, the scene of the drug deal, he finds three people wearing or holding white roses. Heiji trasmits images of the three people to Conan using his cell phone.

Conan, Genta, and Mitsuhiko enter the Teimuzu River Kite Flying Event. Renno and Yatsukoshi form the opposing team. Yatsukoshi holds the kite string while Renno holds their kite and speaks on the phone with his wife Takami. 
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Le tournoi de cerfs-volants de la Tamizu (1re partie)

REGULAR.description:
Renno is led between two posts without a rope barrier and falls into the river. Yatsukoshi, who had feelings for Renno`s mistress, Kakura, whose younger sister had her emotions toyed with, and Takami, whose husband cheated on her, all had motives.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Le tournoi de cerfs-volants de la Tamizu (2e partie)

REGULAR.description:
Conan, Agasa, and the kids visit a boarding house where they are greeted by Ryoko, Aya, and Juri, the three sisters who manage the building. Conan happens upon Aya and Juri`s boyfriend Masahiko arguing. Aya is strongly opposed to Juri`s relationship with Masahiko, who is known for being a bad boy.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Cherche fianc dans tempte de neige
The Lover Gone Missing in a Snowstorm

REGULAR.description:
Conan and his friends search for Ai, who disappeared on her way home from shopping. She is bound and imprisoned by a robber inside the home of her recent acquaintance Higaki Mitsuru along with Mitsuru herself. 
Source: crunchyroll

While Conan and his friends are on their way home from school, a man being chased by the police grabs Ayumi and uses her as a shield. Later, the man passes out from an injury on the back of his head. Emergency medical doctor Kido and nurse Natsumi treat the man, but he remains unconscious and in serious condition.
Source: crunchyroll

A visitor named Reina is killed at Haido Central Hospital. The cause of death is asphyxiation caused by cyanide. Inspector Megure suspects hospital patient Juri and visitors Katsuki and Tokie, who were drinking tea with the victim.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Un th sous haute tension (1re partie)

REGULAR.description:
The police fail to find the container used to hold the poison that killed Reina in the hospital room, and Megure believes it`s likely the culprit took it outside to dispose of it. 
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Un th sous haute tension (2e partie)

REGULAR.description:
Conan and Ran go to the Beika Aquarium where Ran and Shinichi once went on a date. During their date, a man was stabbed to death. The knife used in the stabbing was modified to prevent the victim`s blood from getting on the culprit.
Source: crunchyroll

While Shinichi and Ran are on a date at the Beika Aquarium, Shumoto is stabbed to death. Shinichi and Inspector Megure question Naho, Kanoko, and Jinbe, the people Shumoto was communicating with using his phone. 
Source: crunchyroll

An exhibition of Munch`s work is being held at the Suzuki Museum. Munch`s "Despair" and "Anxiety" are delivered to Narita Airport and packed by shipping company president Shimamura and his employees. Later, the truck transporting "Despair" and "Anxiety" depart for the Suzuki Museum, with the limousine carrying Conan, Ran, and Jirokichi following close behind.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Le Cri de Munch a disparu !

REGULAR.description:
Inspector Megure asks Kogoro for help disguising himself as a famous safecracker and infiltrating a gang of thieves. However, the gang boss Mr. Head sees through his disguise. The man who killed Head`s son is among his subordinates, and he instructs Kogoro to work with the gang as planned to determine the killer`s identity.
Source: crunchyroll

Conan and Kogoro are taken to a warehouse by the gang of thieves to wait for their boss Mr. Head. Suddenly Head`s metallic altered voice comes over the speakers. Kogoro looks at his watch and panics when he sees the time is 2:30 in the morning. If he doesn`t determine who killed Head`s son by dawn, Ran will be killed by an assassin.
Source: crunchyroll

Conan, Ayumi, Genta, and Mitsuhiko meet the Silver Detectives Tokunaga, Mutsuhiko, Ginta, and Yasuko who find a stolen bicycle. The next day, a young man named Kuroda is found dead in his home. The Silver Detectives are the first to discover the body. While pursuing a hooligan they caught littering, they chased him into the house where they found the body. 
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Detective Boys vs the Silver Detectives

REGULAR.description:
Kogoro is hired to find the missing painter Aoki by his wife. Conan determines Aoki is in Tokugawa Prefecture`s Uozo from the painting Aoki sent his wife Midori. Kogoro, Conan, Ran, and Midori discover Aoki`s drowned corpse in Uozu. They investigate the inn where Aoki was staying and interview the manager Hayashi. When Conan sees the painting in the photo, he noticies something was added. The data from the day Aoki took the photo had been erased from his digital camera. Later, permanent part-timer Akagi, traveler Shirakawa, and fisherman Ishiguro all emerge as suspects...
Source: crunchyroll

Amuro witnesses a woman pushed from the top of the stairs at Haido Park. However, he doesn`t see the culprit`s face. The unconscious and gravely injured woman pushed from the stairs is Jodie`s friend and Haido Elementary School teacher Natsuko. Conan and Jodie head to the park and determine Natsuko was attacked somewhere else, and it soon becomes clear she was assaulted at the school. Later, Megure and the police question her coworker Sugamoto, who tried to give Natsuko a ride home, and Ueno and Kandachi, parents of students with appointments to see Natsuko...
Source: crunchyroll

Elementary school teacher Natsuko is struck while working at school and pushed off the stairs in front of the park. Conan and his companions question Sugamoto, another teacher who had planned to walk her home, and parents Ueno and Kandachi, who had appointments to meet with Natsuko. Conan notices something strange while listening to their stories. Later, the police review a photo of the answer sheets Natsuko was grading. Jodie and Camel fail to discover any information that could help them solve the crime from the photo, but Amuro and Conan realize who the culprit is after seeing the picture.
Source: crunchyroll

When Conan hears Camel`s story, he realizes Vermouth disguised herself as Jodie and spoke with him. Conan is frustrated the he acted just as Bourbon (Amuro) and Vermouth planned. Amuro meets with Vermouth, who is still disguised as Jodie. She informs him she learned from Camel that Kusuda shot himself. Amuro responds that there was another burned man who was shot in the head when Kusuda disappeared with thoughts of FBI agent Akai Shuichi on his mind. Amuro deduces Akai is still alive, but...
Source: crunchyroll

Amuro visits Okiya at the Edo family home and begins explaining how one corpse was swapped out for another. Akai was shot in the head and burned along with his car at Raiha Pass. However, Amuro believes Akai switched his own body out for Kusuda`s and is in fact still alive. Amuro explains Akai`s trick step by step to Okiya. Meanwhile, Jodie was thinking the same thing as Amuro. Amuro reasons the body swap was planned not by Akai but by Conan. Amuro then asks Okiya to remove his mask. He is certain Okiya is Akai, but...
Source: crunchyroll

Akai suddenly appears in the back seat of Jodie`s car and fires at the secret police`s vehicles. The bullet strikes a tire, and the FBI agents successfully shake off the secret police. Meanwhile, at the Kudo family home Amuro`s subordinates inform him Akai shot out a tire, causing their cars to crash. Later, Jodie`s car returns to the crash site. Akai takes a cell phone from the secret police and begins speaking to Amuro (Bourbon). He tells him it was a mistake to let Conan know he had the nickname Zero. Akai knew who Amuro truly was...
Source: crunchyroll

Sonoko`s acquaintance Chikada Eimi has her hair cut by someone at high school. Three days earlier and the day before, other students were the victims similar incidents. Before the incidents, warning letters were left in the box of Club Orihime, the romantic help desk Eimi and her friends set up at the school. This morning they received a letter stating, "EC will be brought to justice!" The letters are the initials of the victim. At the scene of the crime, they find a new letter stating, "TB dies as sundown tonight!" Only two hours remain until sunset. To prevent another incident from occurring, Conan and his friends search for a student with the initials TB...
Source: crunchyroll

Haneda Shukichi, also known as Taiko Meijin, takes on Katsumata Chikara in a meijin title match in Yamanashi Prefecture. Just before the second day`s match begins, Shukichi receives a threatening letter from a man calling himself the Headless Shogi Player who claims to have kidnapped Shukichi`s girlfriend Miyamoto Yumi. In order to save Yumi, Shukichi announces he needs time to think and takes a taxi to Tokyo. Interpreting the code labelled "first game," Shukichi arrives at Meiji Jingu where he runs into Conan and his friends as they visit power spots. The code pointed to Kato Kiyomasa`s well. After hearing about the situation, Conan searches the area around the well and discovers the second game`s code left behind by the culprit...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Match pour le titre d`un Taik amoureux (1re partie)

REGULAR.description:
During his Meijin title match, Haneda Shukichi receives a threatening letter from a man calling himself the Headless Shogi Player who claims to have kidnapped his girlfriend Yumi. Conan solves the second game`s code and arrives at a grave on Yureizaka.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Match pour le titre d`un Taik amoureux (2de partie)

REGULAR.description:
Conan and his friends go to a hotel pool where Nagami, daughter of the president of Oiso Finance, drowns to death. She had been wearing a diving tank and searching the pool for her lost necklace. Based on the crime scene, Inspector Megure believes it may have been an accident. However, the hotel bellboys claim the body in the pool suddenly appeared.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Manatsu no Pool ni Shizumu Nazo (Zenpen)
Mystre estival au fond d`une piscine (1re partie)
The Mystery Sinking in the Midsummer Pool (Part 1)

REGULAR.description:
Nagami`s body is discovered in the hotel pool. Megure questions Samaki, Hamaka, and Toyoshima regarding the actions they took after they left Nagami alone in the pool. According to the pool reception staff, between the presumed hour of Nagami`s death between noon and 1 PM, Toyoshima, Samaki, and Hamaka each came to the pool in that order. Later, the bellboys describe the situation at the pool while they were searching for Nagami, leading Conan and Sera to investigate the pool and discover which of her three acquaintances murdered her. They reproduce the manner in which the body disappeared in an experiment, bringing them closer to the culprit...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Manatsu no Pool ni Shizumu Nazo (Kouhen)
Mystre estival au fond d`une piscine (2de partie)
The Mystery Sinking in the Midsummer Pool (Part 2)

REGULAR.description:
A weather forecaster falls to her death after leaning on a second-floor railing, but Conan notices several suspicious things about the body.
Source: Wikipedia

Supermarket Beikado employee Kanzaki receives death threats over the phone. He hires Kogoro to investigate the threats, but Kogoro believes it to be a prank played by a friend. However, an incident occurs the following day on Sunday. A man wearing a ski mask appears at Beikado. While shouting, "Die, Kanzaki," he stabs the man dressed in Beikado`s mascot Bekapon costume and runs away. The victim is employee Shimomura. Every Sunday, Kanzaki interacts with customers dressed as Bekapon, but due to a stomach ache, Shimomura wore the costume in his place. Megure believes the culprit accidentally stabbed Shimomura, but Conan notices something puzzling about the case...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Bekapon et la promo qui tue

REGULAR.description:
Conan and friends witness waiter Someya punching his coworker Nashimoto at a family restaurant. Nearby, Chie trembles in fear for some reason. Three days later, Detective Takagi is escorting Someya to the Metropolitan Police Department in a patrol car, and Someya bungles his escape attempt. Takagi and Someya find themselves alone and handcuffed together. Takagi tries to determine why Someya attempted to flee, but... Conan learns about their situation while watching the news and goes to question Nashimoto. Nashimoto confesses Chie was being talked by Someya. While it`s likelly Someya will go to see Chie, Conan thinks something seems not quite right...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Detective Takagi on the Run in Handcuffs
L`Inspecteur Takagi menott et en cavale

REGULAR.description:
Conan and his friends notice a young boy looking at an apartment from an alleyway and call out to him. The woman who lives in the apartment asked the boy to call the police if she didn`t exit her room after three men came and left her apartment, as it would mean she was likely dead. Conan and his friends discover scriptwriter Yasue dead from hanging in the room. Based on the situation, Megure determines it was a murder. However, the men Shibakaru, Sakaba, and Habanaka who visited the room all claim she was already dead when they came to the room. The case has three first discoverers...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Les trois premiers sur les lieux (1re partie)

REGULAR.description:
Scriptwriter Yasue is found dead in her apartment hanging from a noose. Shibakaru, Sakaba, and Hamanaka all testify she was already dead when they visited her apartment during the presumed time of her death, and Megure believes she may have killed herself. Near the body are scattered 500 thousand yen and roughly a hundred pages of manuscript paper, but Megure determines they would not have been enough to stand on. After questioning, Conan uses his smart phone to investigate the three year old case of a group of thieves who murdered a couple and stole two million yen and learns the name of Yasue`s young friend is Ganno Mamoru. Conan has already arrived at the truth of the situation.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Les trois premiers sur les lieux (2de partie)

REGULAR.description:
Kogoro, Conan, and Ran accompany actresses Haneki Ryo and Sawazaki Reina to the on-location shoot of their gourmet travels TV show. After several attempts on her life, Ryo feels she is in danger. Kogoro is hired to protect Ryo as her bodyguard and determine who is trying to kill her.
Source: crunchyroll

On her way home from school, Ayumi sees Makabe carrying the unconscious body of his wife Yuri to his car. Believing the young married woman she sometimes visited was murdered by her husband, Ayumi and the Detective Boys return to the house to investigate. They are confronted by Makabe while they are looking around the yard. When they ask him where his wife is, he answers that she is in the mountains. Conan and his friends also question a deliveryman who says he heard someone scream in the house the day before. Convinced that murder is a real possibility, they enter the house using a spare key and find a mysterious doll that was not there before as well as dried blood on the floor...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Le secret de la jeune pouse disparue
The Secret of the Missing Young Lady

REGULAR.description:
Mystery writer Kanbayashi falls to his death in the alley between apartment buildings A and B. He fell from the hallway of the fifth floor of building A where his office is located. When he fell, for some reason Kanbayashi changed from his socks into sneakers and was wearing gloves. Megure questions the victim`s wife Seiko and first one to discover the body as well as Sugiyama, building A`s security guard. It seems Kanbayashi and Seiko were a couple of lovebirds. As the police proceed with the investigation, an accident, murder, and suicide all seem like possibilities. Countless mysteries surround the death, and Kanbashi`s actions were mysterious as well. Conan narrows his focus and quickly draws closer to the truth of the fall, but...
Source: crunchyroll

Conan unexpectedly finds himself helping college student Funako find Hikone, a job-hopper who has been missing for two days. They visit Hikone`s apartment and meet college stduent Kiyose who lives on his right and former office worker Nashida who lives on his left, but gain no useful information from either of them.
Source: crunchyroll

Conan witnesses office worker Fukurokoji Sadao fall off the roof of a ten story building. Fukurokoji seems to be falling directly towards office worker Komatsu Hitoshi, who is standing in the alleyway, but Conan kicks a ball into him, and he falls into a nearby heap of garbage and survives. At first it was thought to be an attempted suicide by Fukurokoji, but Inspector Megure determines someone carried the plastered drunk Fukurokoji to the roof and pushed him off, making it an attempted murder. After investigating the rooftop, Conan questions Komatsu, and he deduces that the murderer was attempting to kill not only Fukurokoji, but Komatsu as well. He tries to find someone bearing a grudge against them both, but...
Source: crunchyroll

Conan, Genta, Mitsuhiko, Ayumi, and Ai go to the site of a demolished mansion owned by Professor Agasa`s acquaintance to practice soccer, but when they get there they find the police conducting an investigation. The body of a man was found floating in the pool inside the lot. He died to a blow to the back of the head by a blunt object, and the gate to the lot was unlocked by Agasa, who arrived earlier. The lot is surrounded by a brick wall, and on top of the wall are glass shards and barbed wire. The gate was last opened three days prior, but the victim is presumed to have died before midnight last night. The incident occurred in a roofless locked lot. The Detective Boys try to tackle the locked room mystery, but...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Mystre en chambre close pour les Detective Boys
The Detective Boys` Locked Room Mystery Battle

REGULAR.description:
The soon to be five year old daughter Reina of black marketing lending company president Saeki and his wife Hiroko is kidnapped. The kidnapper demands they bring a 100 million yen ransom to Beika Central Park. He choosestheir housekeeper Suzuko to transport the money, and Conan finds it odd he didn`t choose a family member. Following Kogoro`s advice, Megure has GPS transmitters attached to the bag containing the ransom money, under the car, and in the brooch on Suzuko`s breast. After arriving at the park, wary of transmitters, the kidnapper instructs Suzuko to change cars and bags over the phone. Furthermore, the kidnapper issues instructions to Suzuko to outwit the police and foil their plans...
Source: crunchyroll

During a visit to Tottori, Kogoro, Conan, and Ran come across a case. Shuko, wife of the Kumado family`s eldest son, had her hands and feet bound by a robber, and the family`s heirloom incense burner was stolen. A pedant found at the crime scene casts suspicion on the family`s former housekeeper Naomi, but Kogoro and his family saw her at the sand museum at the time of the crime. Later, head of the household Kumado Isao receives an e-mail on his phone demanding 10 million yen in exchange for the incense burner. Kogoro suspects the crime was committed by a family member who was trying to frame Naomi, and investigates the alibis of Isao, eldest daughter Makie, eldest son Soichi, and second son Junji, but...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Jeu de piste  Tottori (1re partie : Kurayoshi)
The Tottori Sand Dunes Mystery Tour (Kurayoshi Arc)

REGULAR.description:
The heirloom incense burner of the Kumado family, a prominent local family, is stolen. The thief returns the incense burner, but Detective Yamane follows Kogoro`s theory that a member of the family is the thief and thoroughly investigates the alibis of Iwao, Makie, Soichi, and Junji. Conan finds Naomi`s alibi odd and questions her uncle Adachi. According to him, two years ago Naomi witnessed Shuko meeting with a man on the Tottori sand dunes and had been using the information to blackmail her. Hearing Adachi`s story, Conan realizes why Shuko had been tied up and draws closer to the truth behind the case... However, the real crime is about to occur...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Jeu de piste  Tottori (2e partie : Tottori)
The Tottori Sand Dunes Mystery Tour (Tottori Arc)

REGULAR.description:
Three arson cases occur at children`s playgrounds. Conan and his friends conduct a stake out at the lunch vendor used by the man they saw running from the crime scene. Last year, four fires were started at children`s playgrounds, but the suspect was never arrested. Kamaishi, the man they saw the previous night, appears at the lunch vendor, and Conan and his friends follow him. Later, a fire is started at the same playground where the previous year`s fourth fire occurred. Apparently Kamaishi was also watching the area to catch the arsonist. The next morning, the Detective Boys and Kamaishi go to investigate the fires together. Conan visits the various crime scenes and notices a certain rule...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Une prvention du feu seme d`embches

REGULAR.description:
Conan prevents an accident involving a out-of-control car with no working breaks. Someone poked holes in the brake hose, and the police investigate the incident as an attempted murder. The driver Hosoo was on his way to deliver a valuable double-sided mask to Ichikawa Ebizo, who is rehearsing at the kabuki theater. Ebizo plans to use the mask at next month`s performance of "Nanatsu Men." The chairman Matsubara takes the mask from Hosoo and keeps it in a locker during rehearsal, but the next morning, they discover the mask has been stolen. Hosoo`s secretary Takahashi is also found dead inside a car. In the passenger seat is an empty duralumin case that contained the mask. Conan investigates the rehearsal space and determines it is very likely the thief is involved in the play, and Ebizo is moved by Conan`s sharp detective skills. Later, Conan and Ebizo look for the thief together...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Conan and Ebizo`s Kabuki Juhachiban Mystery (Part 1)
Conan to Ebizou: Kabuki Juuhachiban Mystery (Zenpen)
Conan, Ebiz et le mystre d`un classique du kabuki (1re partie)

REGULAR.description:
While on his way to meet Kaneko, Conan is kidnapped. After losing consciousness, Conan awakens in the dark basement of a building being demolished. From overhead he hears the defeaning roar of heavy machinery drilling through concrete.
